<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title"><strong>S.E.C. Turns Its Eye to Hidden Fees in Mutual Funds  </strong> <span class="divider"> | </span></span> First Eagle Investment Management reached an agreement with the S.E.C., and it might just be the start of the commissionâs crackdown on fund companiesâ hidden fees.<br /><span class="kicker"><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2015/09/27/business/sec-turns-its-eye-to-hidden-fees-in-mutual-funds.html">Fair Game &#187;</a></span><span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span><span class="kicker"><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2015/09/27/business/not-naming-the-names-readers-respond-to-an-sec-investigation.html">Letters: Not Naming the Names: A Reader Responds to an S.E.C. Investigation</a> <span class="timestamp" data-eastern-timestamp="1:10 PM" data-utc-timestamp="1443287404"></span></span></p>
